# Cyrius — Compiler Field Notes (Index)
# Compiler-internal training material for agents modifying or
# debugging the cyrius compiler. Topical organization (not
# chronological — for chrono narrative see retros/).
#
# Refreshed 2026-05-02 at v5.8.19 after the language/ split-
# pattern was applied to compiler/. Pre-refresh layout was
# chronological per-version (v3.cyml / v4.cyml / v5_*.cyml);
# the topical files distill recurring patterns + gotchas with
# cross-refs to retros/ for backstory.

# ─── Design Patterns (patterns.cyml) ─── 7 entries ─────────────────
# Reusable design + convention patterns. Earn their slot when an
# agent is making a structural decision (API surface, dep
# distribution, hook wiring, version-source design).

# ship_now_swap_backend_later                 — Decouple stability contract from impl; ship API via C shim, swap to native later
# dist_bundle_stdlib_dep_convention           — Single-file dist/<name>.cyr; cyrius distlib produces; consumers fetch via cyrius deps
# heap_cap_growth_compiler_grows_to_fit_language — When stdlib pushes a cap, raise the cap. Not the other way around. Reshuffle methodology.
# version_string_via_generated_source_not_hardcoded — Route --version through src/version_str.cyr; bump-script writes; never sed source literals
# stdlib_hook_surface_via_fn_pointer_not_callback_registry — One hook fn-pointer + one symbol-resolver beats N per-concern setters
# object_mode_pic_codegen_no_textrel          — object; emits PIC via LEA [rip+disp32] + R_X86_64_PC32. glibc 2.38+ dlopen-safe.
# research_first_optimizer_dce_cfg_lessons    — Pre-v5.0 research roundup: what maps onto cyrius's single-pass no-IR shape

# ─── Process Methodology (methodology.cyml) ─── 8 entries ──────────
# How to debug, how to scope, how to verify slot premises, how to
# triage cross-repo bug reports. Earn their slot when an agent is
# starting a slot, debugging a regression, or scoping a fix.

# premise_check_at_slot_entry                 — Read code + run 5-line probe BEFORE adopting a pin's stated scope
# perf_test_dont_assume_correctness_isnt_perf — Correctness tests are not performance tests. Add benchmarks before shipping an "optimization."
# verify_outputs_not_just_exit_codes          — sed/grep returning 0 doesn't mean it changed anything. Diff/re-read to confirm.
# verify_slot_premise_before_investing        — Reproduce the failure + inspect the artifact (otool/objdump/xxd) before adopting suspect list
# triage_dep_boundary_per_row_checksum        — "Corrupts at scale" cross-repo: standalone replay + per-row checksum at every dep boundary
# ci_drift_detection_silent_skip_is_false_green — Silent SKIP in CI gates is False-PASS. Every gate must report PASS/FAIL/SKIP explicitly.
# ci_drift_detection_orphaned_path_is_certain_drift — Code paths with no CI gate WILL accumulate silent drift (cx backend, helpers, etc.)
# anticipated_gotcha_pre_flight_v55x          — Record gotchas BEFORE an arc starts; update DURING; archive AFTER as field-notes bundle

# ─── Internal Gotchas (gotchas.cyml) ─── 17 entries ────────────────
# Non-obvious traps an agent will hit when working on cyrius's
# compiler internals. Earn their slot when an agent is debugging a
# cyrius regression that doesn't fit a clean pattern.

# slice_fn_local_layout_flip                  — Pre-§8 16-byte fn-locals overflowed past frame; v5.8.16 layout-flip fixes
# slice_high_half_regalloc_pin                — Phantom slot (no name) gets allocated to register; address-based memory I/O bypass
# tail_call_escape_addr_local                 — return helper(&local); — TCO epilogue deallocates frame; v5.8.16 skips TCO when & in args
# pointer_vs_inline_struct_dispatch           — PARSE_FIELD_LOAD auto-detects pointer-vs-inline via slot lli-1 sentinel; v5.8.17
# stale_fixed_cap_drift                       — Cap check drifts out of sync with allocation; recurring trap class
# stdlib_alloc_grow_step_must_cover_request   — Bump allocator's grow step must cover the requested size
# libssl_needs_fdlopen_not_dynlib_open        — pthread-using libs need glibc's TLS/TCB; use fdlopen, not dynlib
# sysv_odd_stack_args_rsp_alignment           — SysV requires rsp 16-aligned at CALL; odd nextra needs pre-pad
# pp_pass_helpers_take_src_base               — Preprocessor pass helpers must take src_base, not assume S+0 region
# ts_lex_jsx_lookahead_terminators            — TS arrow-fn lookahead must terminate at JSX construct close
# fn_keyword_in_param_position                — `fn` is reserved; using it as a param name surfaces error at the NEXT fn def
# lsp_globals_before_fn_definitions           — Top-level vars must be declared before fn bodies that reference them

# ─── Retros (retros/) ─── narrative ────────────────────────────────
# Per-version chronological narrative — feature lists, release-arc
# retrospectives, post-arc reflections. Duplicates CHANGELOG.md /
# completed-phases.md content; preserved here as cyml for vidya
# consumers. Read for backstory; for current work use the topical
# files above.

